# EditorCommand pattern (undo/redo)

Every user-visible mutation to the SVG must be wrapped in an `EditorCommand` and dispatched through `EditorHistoryService.pushAndExecute(cmd)` so undo/redo works.

## `editor-commands.ts` barrel

[`src/app/models/editor-commands.ts`](src/app/models/editor-commands.ts) is the **History public API**: it re-exports `EditorCommand` / `CompositeCommand`, **narrow ports** from `src/app/history/*.port.ts`, and **all command class implementations**. It lives under `models/` for historical path stability, not because it is pure domain data. When adding features: define or extend a **port** in `history/`, re-export its type from this barrel if command constructors need it, and inject only that port into new commands (e.g. `DrawingStyleDefaultsWritePort` for `UpdateDrawingDefaultsCommand`).

## Structure

Command classes live under `src/app/history/commands/` by domain (`paint/`, `transform/`, `layers/`, `document/`, `path/`), re-exported from [`editor-command-implementations.ts`](src/app/history/commands/editor-command-implementations.ts). The core contract (`EditorCommand`, `CompositeCommand`, …) is in [`src/app/models/editor-command.ts`](src/app/models/editor-command.ts). Paint-only commands may depend on `HistoryPaintPort` — import it directly from `src/app/history/history-paint.port.ts` (it is **not** re-exported from the barrel); selection side effects may use `SelectionSyncPort`. Pointer **transform** commands (`TranslateCommand`, `UnionScaleCommand`, `UnionScaleFromCenterCommand`, `UnionRotateCommand`, `SkewCommand`) take `TransformGestureSvgPort` (`src/app/history/transform-gesture-svg.port.ts`) so they do not depend on the full manipulation façade; **undo** restores matrices via `restoreSelectionTransformsFromSnapshot(shapeIds, snapshot)` on that port (implemented by `SvgSelectionGeometryService`). On the canvas, `TransformGestureDocPort.svgManipulation` is typed as `TransformGestureDocSvgPort` (command surface + bbox / snapshot reads for gestures), still implemented by `SvgManipulationService`. Gestures should pass `transformDoc.commandSvg()` into those commands so the call site names the command seam. **Stroke / dash** commands (`AddStrokeCommand`, `RemoveStrokeCommand`, `SetStrokeCommand`, `StrokeDashArrayCommand`, `StrokeDashOffsetCommand`) take `SelectionPaintStrokeDashSvgPort` (`src/app/history/chrome-editor-apply-svg.port.ts`). **Reorder** undo uses `LayerReorderGroupSvgPort.restoreElementSiblingOrder` (`src/app/history/layers-panel-svg.port.ts`, implemented by `SvgLayerStructureService`). **Clipboard / remove / add shape / path / text content** use `EditorShapeLifecycleSvgPort`; **path data** edits use `PathDataEditorSvgPort`; **path node handle linking** uses `PathNodeHandleLinkSvgPort` (all three in `src/app/history/editor-shape-lifecycle-svg.port.ts`).

```typescript
import type { HistoryPaintPort } from '../history-paint.port'; // not in barrel; import directly

export class MyCommand implements EditorCommand {
  readonly description = 'What the user did';

  constructor(
    private readonly paint: HistoryPaintPort,
    // capture old state in constructor so undo can restore it
    private readonly oldValue: T,
    private readonly newValue: T
  ) {}

  execute(): void { /* apply newValue via paint */ }
  undo(): void    { /* restore oldValue via paint */ }
}
```

## Rules

- **Capture old state in the constructor**, not in `execute()`. The command is created *before* execution.
- **Keep commands stateless after construction** — `execute()` and `undo()` should be idempotent and reentrant (redo calls `execute()` again).
- **Delegate to `SvgManipulationService` or a narrow command port** — commands should not manipulate the DOM directly; call service methods (or ports such as `TransformGestureSvgPort`, `EditorShapeLifecycleSvgPort`) that use SVG.js.
- **Use `CompositeCommand`** to batch related commands (e.g. multi-shape property change) into a single undo step.
- **Toggle commands** (like visibility) can call the same service method in both `execute()` and `undo()` only when the operation is self-inverse.
- When undo requires restoring exact DOM positions (reorder, delete), store insertion indices or serialized markup in the constructor.
